nded or online courses, and for students who need to create video assignments to share with classmates and instructors.       Quick Access        User icon        Access via Blackboard        Check icon        Access Panopto        Envelope icon         Contact Us        Matrix icon                Quick Guide          hide   AVAILABLE TO : Faculty | Students | Staff  FUNDED BY:  University       Answers  Features  More Info         Common Questions   Common Questions   How do I install Panopto?  How do I edit a video in Panopto?  How do I access video statistics in Panopto?  How do I turn my PowerPoint presentation into a video using Panopto?  More…   Other Resources   Manage Videos with Panopto  Short Video Overview and Introduction            Features   Panopto can be used as an integrated tool inside Blackboard and directly in the UIC Panopto website . Instructors can:   Easily capture video on Windows, Mac, and iOS  Easily edit video from any web browser  Upload existing video files and automatically convert them for playback on any device  Search for any word spoken or shown on-screen across every video in their library  Engage students with interactive video players that support multi-camera HD playback, inside-video search, digital notes, and more  Access web-based analytics that provide insights into which videos are most popular, who watched which videos, video engagement, and more            More Info   Compliance  HIPAA protected information should not be recorded or communicated through the Panopto system.  Panopto videos will be deleted from the system after four years.  Requirements  Panopto requires industry-standard PC hardware components. For detailed information see https://support.panopto.com/s/article/viewing-requirements-2  Retention of data in Panopto  Video and related content such as bookmarks and comments are kept on Panopto’s servers for a period of three years since last viewed, then are flagged to be removed.              Google Maps imag